<p>At this point, we have a <code>BattleModel</code> object that's populated with the <code>Programmer</code> and
<code>Project</code> objects sent in the request. To create the battle, we need to use the
<code>BattleManager</code>. Do that with <code>$this-&gt;getBattleManager()</code> - that's just a shortcut
to get the service - <code>-&gt;battle()</code> and pass it <code>$battleModel-&gt;getProgrammer()</code> and
<code>$battleModel-&gt;getProject()</code>:</p>
